  "text": "# Chromium Multi-Process Architecture Key Files\n\nThe Chromium multi-process architecture is defined across several critical C++ source files and Mojo interface definitions:\n\n## 1. RenderProcessHostImpl (Browser-side Renderer Representation)\n**Files:** `content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h` and `.cc`\n**Class:** `RenderProcessHostImpl` (line 195 in header)\n**Purpose:** Represents the browser-side view of a renderer process. This class inherits from `RenderProcessHost` and manages the communication channel between the browser process and individual renderer processes. It handles IPC routing, resource management, and coordination with the Mojo IPC system.\n\n## 2. BrowserMainLoop (Main Browser Process Event Loop)\n**Files:** `content/browser/browser_main_loop.h` and `.cc`\n**Class:** `BrowserMainLoop` (line 106 in header)\n**Purpose:** Implements the main browser process event loop and stages called from `BrowserMainRunner`. It initializes and manages critical browser subsystems including the UI thread, IO thread, media services, and other core browser infrastructure.\n\n## 3. RenderThreadImpl (Renderer Process Main Thread)\n**Files:** `content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h` and `.cc`\n**Class:** `RenderThreadImpl` (defined in header)\n**Purpose:** Represents the main thread of a renderer process where `blink::WebView` instances live. It inherits from `RenderThread`, `ChildThreadImpl`, `mojom::Renderer`, and `viz::mojom::CompositingModeWatcher`. This class routes IPC messages to the appropriate `RenderFrameImpl` instances based on routing IDs.\n\n## 4. ChildProcessLauncher (Child Process Spawner)\n**Files:** `content/browser/child_process_launcher.h` and `.cc`\n**Class:** `ChildProcessLauncher` (line 212 in header)\n**Purpose:** Responsible for asynchronously launching child processes (renderers, GPU process, utility processes, etc.). It avoids blocking the main thread during OS process creation and notifies clients when the process handle is available. It manages process lifecycle, priority adjustments, and Mojo invitation handoff.\n\n## 5. Mojo Interface for Browser-to-Renderer Communication\n**File:** `content/common/renderer.mojom`\n**Interface:** `content.mojom.Renderer` (line 49)\n**Purpose:** Defines the primordial Channel-associated Mojo interface implemented by render processes. This interface is used for implementing browser-to-renderer control messages that need to maintain FIFO ordering with respect to legacy IPC messages. It serves as the primary communication contract between browser and renderer processes.\n\nThese five components work together to form the backbone of Chromium's multi-process architecture: the launcher creates the processes, the RenderProcessHostImpl manages them from the browser side, the RenderThreadImpl manages the renderer-side infrastructure, the BrowserMainLoop coordinates the overall browser process, and the Mojo interface provides the communication mechanism between them."
